post_text:
Good afternoon #SUHSD Community. Many of you have heard the comments shared by State of CA officials in the last couple of days.

With this new information and with an abundance of caution, the Sweetwater Union High School District, along with school district superintendents from across the State of California, are taking a safety-first approach and immediate action to extend the school facility closures through the end of the school year. However, in the future, if the stay-at-home order is lifted and the COVID-19 situation improves, we will certainly do our best to reopen school facilities.

To be clear, the 2019-20 school year is not over, it has just transitioned from classroom instruction into distance learning. As we have been sharing, the specific details on distance learning will be coming in the next few days.

Please see the district website at www.sweetwaterschools.org for the full letter sent to our community today and for more updates in the days to come. Thank you and stay safe!

post_text:
Good morning Sweetwater Community,

After careful consideration, and based on guidance from the State of California, the California Department of Education, and the San Diego County Office of Education, the Sweetwater Union High School District, along with all other public school districts in San Diego County, will be closing all schools and cancelling all school-related activities as of Monday, March 16, 2020 through Friday, April 3, 2020.

Please note that today, schools will be operating as scheduled and it will be business as usual. Joint information will be coming from all of the districts in South County in the coming hours and over the next several days.
text:
Good morning Sweetwater Community,

After careful consideration, and based on guidance from the State of California, the California Department of Education, and the San Diego County Office of Education, the Sweetwater Union High School District, along with all other public school districts in San Diego County, will be closing all schools and cancelling all school-related activities as of Monday, March 16, 2020 through Friday, April 3, 2020.

Please note that today, schools will be operating as scheduled and it will be business as usual. Joint information will be coming from all of the districts in South County in the coming hours and over the next several days.

post_text:
Good evening Sweetwater Union High School District Community! Over the past few days we have seen a growing number of posts about the lack of soap in student bathrooms.

We want to assure you that the schools and the district do have a supply of soap both on campuses and at the district level and dispensers are being filled.

As we posted in our most recent FAQ's re: COVID-19 (located on the SUHSD website and in our last FB post), if there is a problem, we ask that students and parents directly inform school administration and/or the front office staff and it can be reconciled in a timely manner. Custodians check soap dispensers on a daily basis and during this time of heightened health awareness, we will be adding additional routine checks.

The health and wellbeing of your student is a high priority for us and we thank you for your continued partnership and support.

Attention #SUHSD family & community for Castle Park High, Hilltop High, Otay Ranch High & Montgomery High. The City of Chula Vista & San Diego have cancelled the permits for fireworks displays for this Friday‚Äôs Homecoming games. We are aware that fireworks are a time-honored tradition during these events, however due to concerns of severely dry weather, we have been advised against the fireworks & permits have been revoked for all fireworks displays.

In a region that has been deeply affected by wildfires, we want to ensure that the safety of the entire community is a priority. We hope that you understand this situation and we look forward to seeing you all on Friday night!

shared_text:

Omar Mercado

LifeChanger of the Year
November 3, 2018 at 6:30 AM ¬∑

Omar Mercado works directly with at-risk youth at SOUTHWEST HIGH SCHOOL - San Diego, CA and Sweetwater Union High School District. He has a unique approach; he holds restorative conferences as an alternative to suspsending students. These conference repair relationships between students, parents, and teachers.

The Best High Schools in America, Ranked

Joe Little
May 14, 2018 at 3:06 PM ¬∑

How about some GOOD school news? Some of our high schools in Chula Vista, National City, and San Diego ranked in the top 13% out of 20,000 schools nationally. That's something the Sweetwater Union High School District can hang their hat on.

The ranked Sweetwater Schools include Eastlake (#167 in CA and #973 in the U.S.), Olympian (#212 in CA and #1158 in the U.S.), Sweetwater (#308 in CA and #1,623 in the U.S.), Hilltop (#396 in CA and #2,036 in the U.S.), San Ysidro (#420 in CA and #2,172 in the U.S.), Castle Park (#441 in CA and #2,270 in the U.S.), and Montgomery (#453 in CA and #2,356 in the U.S.).
